title: SUV overturns on 5 Freeway in Sun Valley, injuring one
text: SUN VALLEY >> A man was injured Saturday when his SUV overturned and caught fire on the Golden State (5) Freeway in Sun Valley, authorities said. The crash of a gold Nissan Armada was reported at 5:16 p.m. in the right lanes of the north 5 at Lankershim Boulevard, the California Highway Patrol said. “The vehicle was on fire with a person trapped,” the Los Angeles Fire Department’s Erik Scott said. “The fire was extinguished and LAFD cut the roof off the vehicle to extricate the man.” The man was hospitalized in serious condition, Scott said.
